<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by Council Directive 72/166/EEC (4), as amended by Directive 72/430/EEC (5), the Council approximated the laws of the Member States relating to insurance against civil liability in respect of the use of motor vehicles and to the enforcement of the obligation to insure against such liability; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: direktiiviga 72/166/EM&Uuml;, (4) muudetud direktiiviga 72/430/EM&Uuml;, (5) &uuml;htlustas n&otilde;ukogu liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktid, mis k&auml;sitlevad mootors&otilde;idukite kasutamise tsiviilvastutuskindlustust ja sellise vastutuse kindlustamise kohustuse rakendamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 3 of Directive 72/166/EEC requires each Member State to take all appropriate measures to ensure that civil liability in respect of the use of vehicles normally based in its territory is covered by insurance; whereas the extent of the liability covered and the terms and conditions of the insurance cover are to be determined on the basis of those measures; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 72/166/EM&Uuml; artikli 3 kohaselt on iga liikmesriik kohustatud v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed tagamaks, et s&otilde;idukite kasutamisel, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on tema territooriumil, on tsiviilvastutus kaetud kindlustusega; kaetud vastutuse ulatus ja kindlustuskaitse tingimused tuleb kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata k&otilde;nealuste meetmete p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, however, major disparities continue to exist between the laws of the different Member States concerning the extent of this obligation of insurance cover; whereas these disparities have a direct effect upon the establishment and the operation of the common market; </inglise>
<eesti> eri liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktides on siiski m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rseid erinevusi k&otilde;nealuse kindlustuskaitse kohustuse ulatuses; need erinevused m&otilde;jutavad otseselt &uuml;histuru loomist ja toimimist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in particular, the extension of the obligation of insurance cover to include liability incurred in respect of damage to property is justified; </inglise>
<eesti> kindlustuskaitse kohustuse laiendamine on eelk&otilde;ige p&otilde;hjendatud ka varakahjuga kaasnevale vastutusele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the amounts in respect of which insurance is compulsory must in any event guarantee victims adequate compensation irrespective of the Member State in which the accident occurred; </inglise>
<eesti> summad, mille puhul kindlustamine on kohustuslik, peavad igal juhul tagama kannatanutele piisava h&uuml;vitise, olenemata sellest, millises liikmesriigis &otilde;nnetus juhtub; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to make provision for a body to guarantee that the victim will not remain without compensation where the vehicle which caused the accident is uninsured or unidentified; whereas it is important, without amending the provisions applied by the Member States with regard to the subsidiary or non-subsidiary nature of the compensation paid by that body and to the rules applicable with regard to subrogation, to provide that the victim of such an accident should be able to apply directly to that body as a first point of contact; whereas, however, Member States should be given the possibility of applying certain limited exclusions as regards the payment of compensation by that body and of providing that compensation for damage to property caused by an unidentified vehicle may be limited or excluded in view of the danger of fraud; </inglise>
<eesti> tuleb ette n&auml;ha organ, kes tagaks, et kannatanu ei j&auml;&auml;ks h&uuml;vitisest ilma, kui &otilde;nnetuse p&otilde;hjustanud s&otilde;iduk on kindlustamata v&otilde;i tundmatu; ilma, et muudetaks liikmesriikides kohaldatavaid s&auml;tteid, mis k&auml;sitlevad k&otilde;nealuse organi makstava h&uuml;vitise esmaj&auml;rgulist v&otilde;i teisej&auml;rgulist laadi ja regressi suhtes kohaldatavaid eeskirju, on oluline s&auml;testada, et sellises &otilde;nnetuses kannatanu saaks k&otilde;igepealt p&ouml;&ouml;rduda vahetult nimetatud organi poole; liikmesriikidele tuleks anda v&otilde;imalus kohaldada k&otilde;nealuse organi poolt h&uuml;vitise maksmise suhtes teatavaid piirangutega erandeid ja s&auml;testada, et tundmatu s&otilde;iduki poolt varakahju h&uuml;vitamine v&otilde;ib pettuseohu v&auml;ltimiseks olla piiratud v&otilde;i v&auml;listatud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is in the interest of victims that the effects of certain exclusion clauses be limited to the relationship between the insurer and the person responsible for the accident; whereas, however, in the case of vehicles stolen or obtained by violence, Member States may specify that compensation will be payable by the abovementioned body; </inglise>
<eesti> kannatanute huvides on, et teatavate erandiklauslite m&otilde;ju piirduks kindlustusandja ja &otilde;nnetuse p&otilde;hjustanud isiku omavaheliste suhetega; varastatud v&otilde;i v&auml;givaldselt omandatud s&otilde;idukite puhul v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata, et h&uuml;vitist maksab eespool nimetatud organ; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in order to alleviate the financial burden on that body, Member States may make provision for the application of certain excesses where the body provides compensation for damage to property caused by uninsured vehicles or, where appropriate, vehicles stolen or obtained by violence; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse organi finantskohustuste leevendamiseks v&otilde;ivad liikmesriigid s&auml;testada teatava omavastutuse kohaldamise, kui organ maksab h&uuml;vitist kindlustamata s&otilde;idukite v&otilde;i olenevalt asjaoludest varastatud v&otilde;i v&auml;givaldselt omandatud s&otilde;idukite poolt varale tekitatud kahjude eest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the members of the family of the insured person, driver or any other person liable should be afforded protection comparable to that of other third parties, in any event in respect of their personal injuries; </inglise>
<eesti> kindlustatu, s&otilde;idukijuhi v&otilde;i muu &otilde;nnetuse eest vastutava isiku perekonnaliikmetele tuleks isikukahju eest pakkuda kaitset, mis on v&otilde;rreldav kolmandatele isikutele pakutava kaitsega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the abolition of checks on insurance is conditional on the granting by the national insurers' bureau of the host country of a guarantee of compensation for damage caused by vehicles normally based in another Member State; whereas the most convenient criterion for determining whether a vehicle is normally based in a given Member State is the bearing of a registration plate of the State; whereas the first indent of Article 1 (4) of Directive 72/166/EEC should therefore be amended to that effect; </inglise>
<eesti> kindlustuse kontrollimise kaotamine oleneb sellest, kas vastuv&otilde;tva riigi liikluskindlustuse rahvuslik b&uuml;roo tagab h&uuml;vitise kahjude eest, mille on tekitanud s&otilde;iduk, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on teises liikmesriigis; k&otilde;ige mugavam moodus m&auml;&auml;ratlemaks, kas s&otilde;iduki p&otilde;hiasukoht on teatavas liikmesriigis, on selle riigi registreerimism&auml;rk asjaomasel s&otilde;idukil; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks direktiivi 72/166/EM&Uuml; artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 4 esimest taanet vastavalt muuta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in view of the situation in certain Member States at the outset as regards on the one hand the minimum amounts, and on the other hand the cover and the excesses applicable by the abovementioned body in respect of damage to property, provision should be made for transitional measures concerning the gradual implementation in those Member States of the provisions of the Directive concerning minimum amounts and compensation for damage to property by that body, </inglise>
<eesti> pidades silmas l&auml;hteolukorda teatavates liikmesriikides seoses &uuml;hest k&uuml;ljest miinimumsumma ja teisest k&uuml;ljest eespool nimetatud organi poolt varakahjude puhul kohaldatava kindlustuskaitse ja omavastutusega, tuleks s&auml;testada &uuml;leminekumeetmed, et k&otilde;nealustes liikmesriikides k&auml;esoleva direktiivi miinimumsummasid ja nimetatud organi poolt varakahjude eest makstavat h&uuml;vitist k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid j&auml;rk-j&auml;rgult kohaldada, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
